// Verilog-AMS discipline definitions - translated to Piperine HDL
// This file defines the standard disciplines used in analog modeling.
// In Piperine HDL, these disciplines are built-in, so this file
// primarily serves as documentation of the mapping.

// The following disciplines and natures are predefined in Piperine:
// - Electrical: potential=Voltage, flow=Current
// - Voltage: potential discipline
// - Current: flow discipline
// - Magnetic: potential=Magneto_Motive_Force, flow=Flux
// - Thermal: potential=Temperature, flow=Power
// - Optical: for optical signal modeling
// - Kinematic: potential=Position, flow=Force
// - Rotational: potential=Angle, flow=Angular_Force
// - Logic: discrete discipline
// - Discrete: domain discipline

mod disciplines;
endmod